# A-LEG-PrecedentCheck Technical Logic Specification

## 1. Core Logic Definition

### 1.1 Function Signature
```
f(PrecedentCheck) → {validity: boolean, risk_score: float, blocking_conditions: array}
```

### 1.2 Precedent Evaluation Logic

```
DEFINE A-LEG-PrecedentCheck:

INPUT: transaction_context, historical_precedents[], regulatory_constraints[]

PROCESS:
  1. precedent_match_score = Σ(weight_i × similarity(current_tx, precedent_i)) / n
  2. temporal_decay = e^(-λ × Δt)  where λ = 0.0023 (daily decay constant)
  3. adjusted_score = precedent_match_score × temporal_decay × jurisdiction_modifier

  IF adjusted_score ≥ 0.85 THEN
    status = APPROVED_WITH_PRECEDENT
  ELSE IF adjusted_score ≥ 0.60 THEN
    status = REQUIRES_REVIEW
  ELSE
    status = NO_VALID_PRECEDENT

OUTPUT: {status, adjusted_score, matched_precedents[], confidence_interval}
```

### 1.3 Similarity Function

```
similarity(tx_current, tx_precedent) = 
  (0.35 × entity_match) + 
  (0.25 × amount_proximity) + 
  (0.20 × structure_alignment) + 
  (0.15 × temporal_context) + 
  (0.05 × jurisdiction_match)

WHERE:
  entity_match ∈ [0,1] = jaccard_index(entities_current, entities_precedent)
  amount_proximity = 1 - |log(amount_current/amount_precedent)| / max_deviation
  structure_alignment = cosine_similarity(structure_vector_a, structure_vector_b)
  temporal_context = sigmoid(relevance_days, midpoint=365, steepness=0.01)
  jurisdiction_match ∈ {0, 0.5, 1} = categorical_match(jur_a, jur_b)
```

