## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Category Definitions

| BPS Range | Classification | Operational State | Required Action |
|-----------|---------------|-------------------|-----------------|
| 0-15 | NOMINAL | Green | Continue processing |
| 16-35 | ELEVATED | Yellow | Enhanced monitoring |
| 36-60 | DEGRADED | Orange | Incident response initiation |
| 61-85 | CRITICAL | Red | Immediate escalation |
| 86-100 | CATASTROPHIC | Black | System halt + manual override |

### 2.2 Component BPS Calculation Matrix

```
BPS_total = Σ(component_weight × component_score × severity_multiplier)
```

| Component | Weight | Failure Modes | Base Score | Severity Multiplier |
|-----------|--------|---------------|------------|---------------------|
| Precedent DB Availability | 0.25 | Connection timeout, Replica lag | 0-100 | 1.0-2.5 |
| Query Latency | 0.15 | p99 > 500ms, p50 > 100ms | 0-100 | 1.0-1.8 |
| Match Algorithm Accuracy | 0.20 | False positive rate, False negative rate | 0-100 | 1.2-3.0 |
| Regulatory Feed Sync | 0.18 | Stale data > 24h, Missing jurisdictions | 0-100 | 1.5-2.8 |
| Cache Hit Ratio | 0.08 | Ratio < 0.6, Eviction storms | 0-100 | 1.0-1.5 |
| Dependency Health | 0.14 | Upstream failures, Circuit breaker trips | 0-100 | 1.3-2.2 |

### 2.3 BPS Calculation Formula

```
BPS_component = base_score × (1 + (error_rate × 10)) × time_in_state_factor

WHERE:
  time_in_state_factor = min(2.0, 1 + (duration_minutes / 30))

BPS_total = Σ(weight_i × BPS_component_i × severity_multiplier_i)

CIRCUIT_BREAKER_THRESHOLD = 75
AUTOMATIC_FAILOVER_THRESHOLD = 55
```

### 2.4 Failure Mode Decision Tree

```
IF precedent_db_latency > 2000ms:
  BPS_db += 45
  trigger_read_replica_failover()

IF match_false_positive_rate > 0.08:
  BPS_algorithm += 60
  enable_secondary_validation_layer()

IF regulatory_feed_age > 86400s:
  BPS_regulatory += 70
  block_new_transactions(jurisdiction=affected)

IF cache_hit_ratio < 0.40:
  BPS_cache += 35
  initiate_cache_warmup()
  increase_ttl(factor=1.5)
```

