# A-HC-PathValidator Technical Specification

## 1. Core Logic Definition

### 1.1 Functional Purpose
A-HC-PathValidator performs hierarchical path validation for distributed system routing, ensuring path integrity across service mesh topologies with deterministic failure detection.

### 1.2 Validation Algorithm

```
FUNCTION ValidatePath(path: PathObject) -> ValidationResult:

    // Phase 1: Structural Validation
    IF path.segments.length == 0 THEN
        RETURN {valid: false, error: "EMPTY_PATH", bps: 100}

    IF path.segments.length > MAX_DEPTH (default: 64) THEN
        RETURN {valid: false, error: "DEPTH_EXCEEDED", bps: 85}

    // Phase 2: Node Connectivity Validation
    FOR i = 0 TO path.segments.length - 1:
        current_node = path.segments[i]

        // Existence Check
        IF NOT NodeRegistry.exists(current_node.id) THEN
            RETURN {valid: false, error: "NODE_NOT_FOUND", node: i, bps: 95}

        // Health Check
        IF current_node.health_score < HEALTH_THRESHOLD (default: 0.7) THEN
            RETURN {valid: false, error: "UNHEALTHY_NODE", node: i, bps: 75}

        // Edge Validation (for non-terminal nodes)
        IF i < path.segments.length - 1:
            next_node = path.segments[i + 1]
            edge_weight = EdgeMatrix[current_node.id][next_node.id]

            IF edge_weight == NULL OR edge_weight == INFINITY THEN
                RETURN {valid: false, error: "DISCONNECTED_EDGE", edge: [i, i+1], bps: 90}

            IF edge_weight > LATENCY_THRESHOLD (default: 500ms) THEN
                RETURN {valid: false, error: "LATENCY_VIOLATION", edge: [i, i+1], bps: 60}

    // Phase 3: Cycle Detection (Tortoise-Hare)
    visited = HashSet()
    FOR segment IN path.segments:
        IF visited.contains(segment.id) THEN
            RETURN {valid: false, error: "CYCLE_DETECTED", bps: 80}
        visited.add(segment.id)

    // Phase 4: Policy Compliance
    policy_result = PolicyEngine.evaluate(path)
    IF NOT policy_result.compliant THEN
        RETURN {valid: false, error: "POLICY_VIOLATION", details: policy_result, bps: 70}

    // Phase 5: Compute Path Score
    path_score = ComputePathScore(path)

    RETURN {valid: true, score: path_score, bps: 0}
```

### 1.3 Path Score Computation

```
FUNCTION ComputePathScore(path: PathObject) -> Float:

    // Weighted scoring model
    W_latency = 0.35
    W_reliability = 0.30
    W_capacity = 0.20
    W_hops = 0.15

    // Latency Score (inverse normalized)
    total_latency = SUM(EdgeMatrix[path.segments[i]][path.segments[i+1]].latency)
    latency_score = 1 - (total_latency / MAX_ACCEPTABLE_LATENCY)
    latency_score = CLAMP(latency_score, 0, 1)

    // Reliability Score (product of node reliabilities)
    reliability_score = PRODUCT(path.segments[i].reliability FOR i IN range)

    // Capacity Score (minimum bottleneck normalized)
    min_capacity = MIN(EdgeMatrix[path.segments[i]][path.segments[i+1]].capacity)
    capacity_score = min_capacity / BASELINE_CAPACITY
    capacity_score = CLAMP(capacity_score, 0, 1)

    // Hop Score (inverse normalized)
    hop_score = 1 - (path.segments.length / MAX_DEPTH)

    // Final weighted score
    RETURN (W_latency * latency_score) + 
           (W_reliability * reliability_score) + 
           (W_capacity * capacity_score) + 
           (W_hops * hop_score)
```

