# A-EC-DynamicPrice Technical Specification

## 1. Core Algorithm Logic

### 1.1 Price Calculation Function

```
P_final = P_base × D_m × S_m × C_m × T_m × E_m

Where:
├── P_base    = Base product price (USD, float64)
├── D_m       = Demand multiplier ∈ [0.85, 2.50]
├── S_m       = Supply/inventory multiplier ∈ [0.90, 1.80]
├── C_m       = Competition multiplier ∈ [0.75, 1.25]
├── T_m       = Time-decay multiplier ∈ [0.70, 1.15]
└── E_m       = Elasticity multiplier ∈ [0.80, 1.40]
```

### 1.2 Demand Multiplier Derivation

```
D_m = 1 + (α × ln(Q_current / Q_baseline))

Where:
├── α         = Demand sensitivity coefficient = 0.23
├── Q_current = Current demand velocity (units/hour)
├── Q_baseline = Historical baseline demand (units/hour, 30-day rolling avg)

Boundary conditions:
├── IF Q_current / Q_baseline < 0.1 THEN D_m = 0.85
└── IF Q_current / Q_baseline > 15.0 THEN D_m = 2.50
```

### 1.3 Supply Multiplier Derivation

```
S_m = 1 + β × (1 - (I_current / I_optimal))

Where:
├── β         = Supply sensitivity coefficient = 0.65
├── I_current = Current inventory level (units)
├── I_optimal = Optimal inventory threshold (units)

Boundary conditions:
├── IF I_current ≥ I_optimal × 2.0 THEN S_m = 0.90
├── IF I_current ≤ I_optimal × 0.05 THEN S_m = 1.80
└── IF I_current = 0 THEN trigger OUT_OF_STOCK state
```

### 1.4 Competition Multiplier Derivation

```
C_m = 1 - γ × ((P_competitor_avg - P_base) / P_base)

Where:
├── γ         = Competition response coefficient = 0.40
├── P_competitor_avg = Weighted average competitor price

Clamping:
├── C_m = MAX(0.75, MIN(1.25, C_m))
```

### 1.5 Time-Decay Multiplier

```
T_m = 1 - δ × (t_elapsed / t_shelf_life)

Where:
├── δ         = Time decay coefficient = 0.30
├── t_elapsed = Time since product listing (hours)
├── t_shelf_life = Maximum shelf life (hours)

Boundary conditions:
├── IF t_elapsed / t_shelf_life > 0.95 THEN T_m = 0.70
└── IF t_elapsed / t_shelf_life < 0.10 THEN T_m = 1.15
```

### 1.6 Elasticity Multiplier

```
E_m = 1 + ε × (PED_observed - PED_baseline)

Where:
├── ε         = Elasticity adjustment factor = 0.18
├── PED_observed = Observed price elasticity of demand
├── PED_baseline = Category baseline elasticity

PED_observed = (ΔQ/Q) / (ΔP/P)
```

---

## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Scoring Formula

```
BPS_total = Σ(W_i × R_i × I_i)

Where:
├── W_i = Weight factor for component i
├── R_i = Risk probability [0.0, 1.0]
├── I_i = Impact severity [1, 10]
```

### 2.2 Component BPS Matrix

| Component ID | Component Name | Weight (W) | Risk Triggers | Impact (I) | BPS Threshold |
|--------------|----------------|------------|---------------|------------|---------------|
| BPS-001 | Price Calculation Engine | 0.25 | Latency > 50ms, Error rate > 0.1% | 10 | 2.50 |
| BPS-002 | Demand Signal Ingestion | 0.20 | Lag > 5s, Data staleness > 60s | 9 | 1.80 |
| BPS-003 | Inventory Sync Service | 0.18 | Sync delta > 2%, Latency > 200ms | 8 | 1.44 |
| BPS-004 | Competitor Price Feed | 0.12 | Feed age > 300s, Coverage < 80% | 6 | 0.72 |
| BPS-005 | ML Elasticity Model | 0.10 | Inference latency > 100ms, Drift > 15% | 7 | 0.70 |
| BPS-006 | Price Validation Layer | 0.08 | Rejection rate > 5%, False positive > 2% | 8 | 0.64 |
| BPS-007 | Cache Layer (Redis) | 0.05 | Hit rate < 85%, Eviction rate > 10%/min | 5 | 0.25 |
| BPS-008 | Database (Price Store) | 0.02 | Query latency > 20ms, Connection pool > 80% | 9 | 0.18 |

### 2.3 BPS Operational States

```
BPS_total ∈ [0.00, 2.00)  → STATE: NOMINAL
BPS_total ∈ [2.00, 4.00)  → STATE: DEGRADED
BPS_total ∈ [4.00, 6.00)  → STATE: CRITICAL
BPS_total ∈ [6.00, 8.21]  → STATE: FAILURE

Action Matrix:
├── NOMINAL   → Continue operations, standard monitoring
├── DEGRADED  → Alert L2, enable fallback pricing, increase sampling
├── CRITICAL  → Page on-call, activate circuit breakers, static pricing mode
└── FAILURE   → Full fallback to cached prices, incident declaration
```

### 2.4 Cascading Failure Probability

```
P_cascade = 1 - Π(1 - P_failure_i)^(dependency_depth_i)

Critical Path Dependencies:
├── Price Engine → Demand Signal → Inventory Sync (depth: 3)
├── Price Engine → ML Model → Feature Store (depth: 3)
└── Price Engine → Validation → Database (depth: 3)

IF P_cascade > 0.15 THEN trigger preemptive degradation
```

