# A-EC-RestockSim Technical Logic Specification

## 1. System Overview

A-EC-RestockSim is an automated e-commerce inventory restocking simulation engine designed to model, predict, and optimize replenishment cycles under variable demand conditions.

---

## 2. Core Mathematical Models

### 2.1 Demand Forecasting Function

```
D(t) = μ_d + σ_d · Z(t) + S(t) + T(t)

Where:
  D(t)  = Demand at time t
  μ_d   = Mean historical demand
  σ_d   = Demand standard deviation
  Z(t)  = Stochastic noise component (normal distribution)
  S(t)  = Seasonal adjustment factor
  T(t)  = Trend component
```

### 2.2 Economic Order Quantity (EOQ) with Safety Stock

```
EOQ = √((2 · D_annual · C_order) / C_hold)

SS = Z_α · σ_d · √(L)

ROP = (D_avg · L) + SS

Where:
  C_order  = Cost per order placement
  C_hold   = Holding cost per unit per period
  SS       = Safety stock
  Z_α      = Service level z-score (α = 0.95 → Z = 1.645)
  L        = Lead time in periods
  ROP      = Reorder point
```

### 2.3 Inventory Position Function

```
IP(t) = OH(t) + OO(t) - BO(t)

Where:
  IP(t) = Inventory position at time t
  OH(t) = On-hand inventory
  OO(t) = On-order inventory
  BO(t) = Backorders
```

### 2.4 Service Level Calculation

```
SL = 1 - (Σ Stockout_Events / Σ Demand_Cycles)

Fill_Rate = Σ Units_Fulfilled / Σ Units_Demanded
```

---

## 3. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 3.1 BPS Calculation Formula

```
BPS = Σ(W_i · R_i · I_i) / Σ W_i

Where:
  W_i = Weight factor for risk category i
  R_i = Risk probability (0.0 - 1.0)
  I_i = Impact severity (1 - 10)

Critical Threshold: BPS ≥ 7.0
Warning Threshold:  BPS ≥ 4.5
Normal:             BPS < 4.5
```

### 3.2 BPS Risk Category Matrix

| Risk ID | Category | Weight (W) | Risk Indicators | Impact Range |
|---------|----------|------------|-----------------|--------------|
| BPS-001 | Supplier Failure | 0.25 | Lead time variance > 2σ | 8-10 |
| BPS-002 | Demand Spike | 0.20 | D(t) > μ + 3σ | 6-9 |
| BPS-003 | Inventory Depletion | 0.20 | OH(t) < SS | 7-10 |
| BPS-004 | System Latency | 0.10 | API response > P99 | 4-7 |
| BPS-005 | Data Integrity | 0.10 | Checksum failures > 0.1% | 8-10 |
| BPS-006 | Forecast Drift | 0.08 | MAPE > 25% | 5-8 |
| BPS-007 | Order Processing | 0.07 | Queue depth > 10K | 3-6 |

### 3.3 BPS Escalation Logic

```python
def calculate_bps(risk_events: list[dict]) -> float:
    total_weighted_score = 0.0
    total_weight = 0.0

    for event in risk_events:
        w = event["weight"]
        r = event["probability"]
        i = event["impact"]
        total_weighted_score += w * r * i
        total_weight += w

    return total_weighted_score / total_weight if total_weight > 0 else 0.0

def get_bps_status(bps: float) -> str:
    if bps >= 7.0:
        return "CRITICAL"  # Trigger incident, halt simulation
    elif bps >= 4.5:
        return "WARNING"   # Alert on-call, increase monitoring
    else:
        return "NORMAL"    # Continue operations
```

