## 5. SRE Metrics Specification

### 5.1 Service Level Objectives (SLOs)

| Metric | Target | Measurement Window | Burn Rate Alert |
|--------|--------|-------------------|-----------------|
| Simulation Availability | 99.9% | 30-day rolling | 14.4x (1h), 6x (6h) |
| API Latency P50 | ≤ 50ms | 5-minute | N/A |
| API Latency P95 | ≤ 200ms | 5-minute | N/A |
| API Latency P99 | ≤ 500ms | 5-minute | 2x threshold |
| Simulation Accuracy | MAPE ≤ 15% | Per simulation run | N/A |
| Data Consistency | 99.99% | Continuous | Any violation |

### 5.2 Service Level Indicators (SLIs)

```yaml
slis:
  availability:
    formula: "(successful_requests / total_requests) * 100"
    good_event: "response_code < 500 AND response_time < 30s"

  latency:
    formula: "histogram_quantile(0.99, request_duration_seconds)"
    buckets: [0.01, 0.025, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.5, 5.0, 10.0]

  simulation_throughput:
    formula: "rate(simulation_ticks_total[5m])"
    target: ">= 1000 ticks/second per instance"

  error_rate:
    formula: "rate(simulation_errors_total[5m]) / rate(simulation_ticks_total[5m])"
    threshold: "< 0.001"
```

