## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 BPS Calculation Formula

```
BPS = Σ(Wᵢ × Rᵢ × Iᵢ) / N

Where:
  Wᵢ = Weight factor for component i (0.0 - 1.0)
  Rᵢ = Risk probability for component i (0.0 - 1.0)
  Iᵢ = Impact severity for component i (1 - 10)
  N  = Normalization constant = Σ(Wᵢ × 10)
```

### 2.2 Component Risk Matrix

| Component ID | Component Name | Weight (Wᵢ) | Risk Threshold | Impact (Iᵢ) | BPS Contribution |
|--------------|----------------|-------------|----------------|-------------|------------------|
| C-001 | Data Ingestion Pipeline | 0.85 | R ≥ 0.15 | 9 | `0.85 × R × 9` |
| C-002 | Feature Extraction Engine | 0.90 | R ≥ 0.10 | 10 | `0.90 × R × 10` |
| C-003 | Bias Detection Model | 0.95 | R ≥ 0.05 | 10 | `0.95 × R × 10` |
| C-004 | Fairness Scoring Module | 0.92 | R ≥ 0.08 | 9 | `0.92 × R × 9` |
| C-005 | Decision Gateway | 0.88 | R ≥ 0.12 | 8 | `0.88 × R × 8` |
| C-006 | Audit Logger | 0.75 | R ≥ 0.20 | 7 | `0.75 × R × 7` |
| C-007 | Model Drift Detector | 0.80 | R ≥ 0.18 | 8 | `0.80 × R × 8` |
| C-008 | Protected Class Validator | 0.93 | R ≥ 0.07 | 10 | `0.93 × R × 10` |

### 2.3 BPS Severity Classification

```
BPS_SEVERITY = {
    "NOMINAL":    BPS < 0.15,
    "ELEVATED":   0.15 ≤ BPS < 0.35,
    "WARNING":    0.35 ≤ BPS < 0.55,
    "CRITICAL":   0.55 ≤ BPS < 0.75,
    "BREAKDOWN":  BPS ≥ 0.75
}
