# A-LS-MigratProof Technical Logic Specification

## 1. System Definition

**A-LS-MigratProof** (Automated Logical State Migration Proof) is a deterministic verification system that validates data integrity, state consistency, and operational continuity during migration operations.

---

## 2. Core Logic Functions

### 2.1 State Hash Verification

```
H(S) = SHA-256(serialize(S_source)) 
H(S') = SHA-256(serialize(S_target))

VALID iff H(S) == H(S') ∧ |S| == |S'| ∧ ∀i: S[i] ≡ S'[i]
```

### 2.2 Migration Proof Formula

```
MigratProof(t) = {
    integrity:    I(t) = Σ(checksum_match[i]) / n == 1.0
    completeness: C(t) = |records_target| / |records_source| == 1.0
    consistency:  K(t) = ∀r ∈ R: schema(r_src) ≅ schema(r_tgt)
    ordering:     O(t) = sequence_preserved(S_src, S_tgt) ∈ {0,1}
}

PROOF_VALID = I(t) ∧ C(t) ∧ K(t) ∧ O(t) == TRUE
```

### 2.3 Rollback Decision Function

```
R(t) = {
    ROLLBACK    if BPS(t) > θ_critical ∨ I(t) < 0.9999
    PAUSE       if θ_warning < BPS(t) ≤ θ_critical
    CONTINUE    if BPS(t) ≤ θ_warning
}

where:
    θ_warning  = 0.15
    θ_critical = 0.35
```

---

## 3. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 3.1 Risk Category Weights

| Category | Symbol | Weight (w) | Description |
|----------|--------|------------|-------------|
| Data Loss | DL | 0.30 | Unrecoverable record loss |
| Schema Drift | SD | 0.20 | Type/structure mismatch |
| Latency Breach | LB | 0.15 | SLO timing violations |
| Connection Failure | CF | 0.15 | Network/auth failures |
| Checksum Mismatch | CM | 0.12 | Hash verification failure |
| Ordering Violation | OV | 0.08 | Sequence integrity loss |

### 3.2 BPS Calculation

```
BPS(t) = Σ(w_i × severity_i × occurrence_rate_i)

where:
    severity_i ∈ [0.0, 1.0]
    occurrence_rate_i = failures_i / total_operations

BPS_composite = (w_DL × S_DL × R_DL) + 
                (w_SD × S_SD × R_SD) + 
                (w_LB × S_LB × R_LB) + 
                (w_CF × S_CF × R_CF) + 
                (w_CM × S_CM × R_CM) + 
                (w_OV × S_OV × R_OV)
```

### 3.3 BPS Threshold Matrix

| BPS Range | State | Action | Alert Level |
|-----------|-------|--------|-------------|
| 0.00 - 0.05 | NOMINAL | Continue | None |
| 0.05 - 0.15 | DEGRADED | Monitor | P3 |
| 0.15 - 0.25 | WARNING | Throttle | P2 |
| 0.25 - 0.35 | CRITICAL | Pause | P1 |
| 0.35 - 1.00 | FAILURE | Rollback | P0 |

### 3.4 Severity Classification

```
severity(event) = {
    1.0  if event.type == CORRUPTION ∨ event.type == TOTAL_LOSS
    0.8  if event.type == PARTIAL_LOSS ∧ affected_ratio > 0.1
    0.6  if event.type == SCHEMA_VIOLATION
    0.4  if event.type == TIMEOUT ∧ retry_exhausted
    0.2  if event.type == RECOVERABLE_ERROR
    0.1  if event.type == WARNING
}
```

