### 4.1 Weight Normalization Constraint

```
Validation Rule: Σ(weights) = 1.0 ± 0.001

Implementation:
if |Σ(w) - 1.0| > 0.001:
    raise ValidationError("WEIGHT_SUM_INVALID", sum=Σ(w))
```

# A-OSI-ArtifactAudit Technical Specification

## 1. Core Logic Definition

### 1.1 Artifact Audit State Machine

```
States: {PENDING, SCANNING, VALIDATING, AUDITED, FAILED, QUARANTINED}

Transitions:
  PENDING → SCANNING     : trigger(audit_request) ∧ resource_available
  SCANNING → VALIDATING  : scan_complete ∧ ¬critical_violation
  SCANNING → QUARANTINED : critical_violation_detected
  VALIDATING → AUDITED   : validation_pass ∧ signature_valid
  VALIDATING → FAILED    : validation_fail ∨ signature_invalid
  FAILED → PENDING       : retry_count < max_retries
  FAILED → QUARANTINED   : retry_count ≥ max_retries
```

### 1.2 Audit Decision Function

```
f(artifact) = {
  PASS    if Σ(weight_i × check_i) ≥ θ_pass ∧ critical_checks = ∅
  WARN    if Σ(weight_i × check_i) ≥ θ_warn ∧ critical_checks = ∅
  FAIL    if Σ(weight_i × check_i) < θ_warn ∨ |critical_checks| > 0
}

Where:
  θ_pass = 0.95
  θ_warn = 0.80
  weight_i ∈ [0.0, 1.0]
  check_i ∈ {0, 1}
```

---

## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Category Definitions

| Risk ID | Category | Description | Weight |
|---------|----------|-------------|--------|
| R001 | Integrity | Checksum/signature mismatch | 1.0 |
| R002 | Provenance | Unknown or untrusted source | 0.9 |
| R003 | Compliance | Policy violation detected | 0.85 |
| R004 | Vulnerability | CVE presence in artifact | 0.95 |
| R005 | Staleness | Artifact age exceeds TTL | 0.6 |
| R006 | Size Anomaly | Deviation from baseline >3σ | 0.7 |
| R007 | Dependency | Unresolved/circular deps | 0.75 |
| R008 | Metadata | Missing required fields | 0.5 |

### 2.2 BPS Calculation Formula

```
BPS = 100 × (1 - Π(1 - (P_i × I_i × W_i)))

Where:
  P_i = Probability of failure mode i occurring [0.0, 1.0]
  I_i = Impact severity of failure mode i [0.0, 1.0]
  W_i = Weight factor from risk category [0.0, 1.0]

Thresholds:
  BPS < 15  : LOW_RISK      → Auto-approve
  BPS 15-40 : MEDIUM_RISK   → Manual review queue
  BPS 40-70 : HIGH_RISK     → Senior approval required
  BPS > 70  : CRITICAL_RISK → Auto-reject + incident
```

### 2.3 BPS Operational Matrix

```
┌─────────────────┬────────┬────────┬────────┬──────────┐
│ Failure Mode    │ P(low) │ P(med) │ P(high)│ Max BPS  │
├─────────────────┼────────┼────────┼────────┼──────────┤
│ Checksum Fail   │ 0.01   │ 0.05   │ 0.15   │ 15.0     │
│ Sig Invalid     │ 0.02   │ 0.08   │ 0.20   │ 20.0     │
│ CVE Critical    │ 0.05   │ 0.15   │ 0.35   │ 33.25    │
│ CVE High        │ 0.10   │ 0.25   │ 0.45   │ 38.475   │
│ Source Untrust  │ 0.03   │ 0.10   │ 0.25   │ 22.5     │
│ Policy Violate  │ 0.08   │ 0.20   │ 0.40   │ 34.0     │
│ Dep Resolution  │ 0.15   │ 0.30   │ 0.50   │ 37.5     │
│ Metadata Miss   │ 0.20   │ 0.35   │ 0.55   │ 27.5     │
└─────────────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┴──────────┘

Compound BPS (worst case all high):
BPS_max = 100 × (1 - (0.85 × 0.80 × 0.65 × 0.615 × 0.775 × 0.66 × 0.625 × 0.725))
BPS_max = 100 × (1 - 0.0847) = 91.53
```

