# A-OSI-TruthBPS Technical Specification

## 1. Core Logic Definition

### 1.1 Truth Verification Function

```
T(x) = Σᵢ₌₁ⁿ [wᵢ × V(xᵢ)] / Σᵢ₌₁ⁿ wᵢ

Where:
- T(x) ∈ [0, 1] = Truth confidence score
- V(xᵢ) = Verification function for claim component i
- wᵢ = Weight coefficient for source reliability
- n = Total verification vectors
```

### 1.2 Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Formula

```
BPS = 1 - ∏ᵢ₌₁ᵐ (1 - Pᵢ × Iᵢ)

Where:
- BPS ∈ [0, 1] = System breakdown probability
- Pᵢ = Probability of failure mode i
- Iᵢ = Impact coefficient of failure mode i
- m = Total failure modes identified
```

### 1.3 Operational State Machine

```
States: {NOMINAL, DEGRADED, CRITICAL, BREAKDOWN}

Transitions:
  NOMINAL → DEGRADED    : BPS > 0.25
  DEGRADED → CRITICAL   : BPS > 0.50
  CRITICAL → BREAKDOWN  : BPS > 0.75
  ANY → NOMINAL         : BPS < 0.20 ∧ T(x) > 0.85
```

---

## 2. BPS Failure Risk Matrix

### 2.1 Layer-Mapped Failure Modes (OSI-Aligned)

| Layer | Failure Mode | P(failure) | Impact (I) | BPS Contribution | MTTR Target |
|-------|--------------|------------|------------|------------------|-------------|
| L7-Application | Truth assertion corruption | 0.08 | 0.95 | 0.076 | 15min |
| L7-Application | Schema validation bypass | 0.05 | 0.90 | 0.045 | 10min |
| L6-Presentation | Encoding/format mismatch | 0.12 | 0.60 | 0.072 | 20min |
| L6-Presentation | Serialization failure | 0.07 | 0.70 | 0.049 | 15min |
| L5-Session | Context state loss | 0.15 | 0.80 | 0.120 | 25min |
| L5-Session | Session hijack/corruption | 0.03 | 0.98 | 0.029 | 5min |
| L4-Transport | Packet integrity failure | 0.04 | 0.85 | 0.034 | 10min |
| L4-Transport | Flow control breakdown | 0.06 | 0.75 | 0.045 | 15min |
| L3-Network | Routing table corruption | 0.09 | 0.88 | 0.079 | 30min |
| L3-Network | Path verification failure | 0.11 | 0.82 | 0.090 | 20min |
| L2-Data Link | Frame validation error | 0.10 | 0.65 | 0.065 | 12min |
| L2-Data Link | MAC address spoofing | 0.02 | 0.92 | 0.018 | 8min |
| L1-Physical | Signal degradation | 0.14 | 0.55 | 0.077 | 45min |
| L1-Physical | Hardware failure | 0.06 | 0.99 | 0.059 | 60min |

### 2.2 Composite BPS Calculation

```
BPS_composite = 1 - ∏(1 - BPSᵢ)
             = 1 - (0.924 × 0.955 × 0.928 × 0.951 × 0.880 × 0.971 × 
                    0.966 × 0.955 × 0.921 × 0.910 × 0.935 × 0.982 × 
                    0.923 × 0.941)
             ≈ 0.612
```

### 2.3 Risk Severity Classification

```
SEVERITY_MATRIX = {
  "SEV1": BPS > 0.75 ∨ (P > 0.10 ∧ I > 0.90),
  "SEV2": BPS ∈ (0.50, 0.75] ∨ (P > 0.15 ∧ I > 0.75),
  "SEV3": BPS ∈ (0.25, 0.50] ∨ (P > 0.20 ∧ I > 0.60),
  "SEV4": BPS ≤ 0.25 ∧ P ≤ 0.20 ∧ I ≤ 0.60
}
```

