## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 BPS Calculation Formula

```
BPS_total = Σ(w_i × R_i × S_i × T_i) / N

Where:
  w_i = Weight factor for risk category i (0.0 - 1.0)
  R_i = Raw risk score (1-100)
  S_i = Severity multiplier (1.0 - 5.0)
  T_i = Time decay factor = e^(-λt), λ = 0.1
  N   = Normalization constant = Σw_i
```

### 2.2 BPS Category Matrix

| Category ID | Risk Domain | Weight (w) | Threshold_Warning | Threshold_Critical | Threshold_Breakdown |
|-------------|-------------|------------|-------------------|--------------------|--------------------|
| BPS-001 | Liquidity Risk | 0.95 | 45 | 70 | 85 |
| BPS-002 | Board Alignment | 0.85 | 40 | 65 | 80 |
| BPS-003 | Regulatory Compliance | 0.90 | 35 | 60 | 75 |
| BPS-004 | Market Position | 0.75 | 50 | 72 | 88 |
| BPS-005 | Operational Continuity | 0.88 | 42 | 68 | 82 |
| BPS-006 | Stakeholder Confidence | 0.80 | 48 | 70 | 85 |
| BPS-007 | Strategic Execution | 0.82 | 44 | 66 | 80 |
| BPS-008 | Talent Retention | 0.70 | 55 | 75 | 90 |
| BPS-009 | Technology Debt | 0.78 | 50 | 73 | 87 |
| BPS-010 | Supply Chain Resilience | 0.83 | 46 | 69 | 84 |

### 2.3 BPS Severity Multiplier Logic

```python
def calculate_severity_multiplier(risk_score: float, category: str) -> float:
    """
    S_i calculation based on risk score bands
    """
    severity_bands = {
        (0, 25): 1.0,
        (25, 50): 1.5,
        (50, 70): 2.5,
        (70, 85): 3.5,
        (85, 100): 5.0
    }

    for (lower, upper), multiplier in severity_bands.items():
        if lower <= risk_score < upper:
            return multiplier
    return 5.0
```

