## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Calculation Formula

```
BPS = (P × I × D) / M

Where:
  P = Probability of occurrence (0.0 - 1.0)
  I = Impact severity (1 - 10)
  D = Detection difficulty (1 - 10)
  M = Mitigation effectiveness (1 - 10)

Risk Classification:
  BPS < 2.0   → LOW (Green)
  BPS 2.0-5.0 → MEDIUM (Yellow)
  BPS 5.0-8.0 → HIGH (Orange)
  BPS > 8.0   → CRITICAL (Red)
```

### 2.2 Failure Mode Matrix

| Failure Mode ID | Description | P | I | D | M | BPS | Classification |
|-----------------|-------------|---|---|---|---|-----|----------------|
| FM-001 | Schema validation bypass | 0.05 | 10 | 3 | 8 | 0.19 | LOW |
| FM-002 | Checksum collision attack | 0.01 | 10 | 8 | 6 | 0.13 | LOW |
| FM-003 | Memory exhaustion (large payload) | 0.15 | 8 | 4 | 5 | 0.96 | LOW |
| FM-004 | Floating-point precision loss | 0.30 | 9 | 7 | 4 | 4.73 | MEDIUM |
| FM-005 | Character encoding corruption | 0.20 | 7 | 6 | 7 | 1.20 | LOW |
| FM-006 | Concurrent write race condition | 0.25 | 9 | 8 | 3 | 6.00 | HIGH |
| FM-007 | Malformed date parsing | 0.35 | 6 | 3 | 8 | 0.79 | LOW |
| FM-008 | Currency conversion drift | 0.40 | 8 | 9 | 5 | 5.76 | HIGH |
| FM-009 | Orphaned transaction reference | 0.20 | 7 | 5 | 6 | 1.17 | LOW |
| FM-010 | Cascading validation timeout | 0.10 | 10 | 6 | 4 | 1.50 | LOW |
| FM-011 | Double-entry imbalance propagation | 0.08 | 10 | 4 | 3 | 1.07 | LOW |
| FM-012 | Upstream dependency failure | 0.45 | 8 | 2 | 6 | 1.20 | LOW |
| FM-013 | State machine deadlock | 0.05 | 10 | 9 | 2 | 2.25 | MEDIUM |
| FM-014 | Audit trail truncation | 0.12 | 9 | 7 | 5 | 1.51 | LOW |
| FM-015 | Regulatory field omission | 0.18 | 10 | 5 | 7 | 1.29 | LOW |

### 2.3 Aggregate Risk Profile

```
Total Weighted BPS = Σ(BPS_i × Weight_i) / n

Critical Path Components:
  - Input Validation Layer:    Σ BPS = 2.08
  - Parse Engine:              Σ BPS = 7.69
  - Transform Pipeline:        Σ BPS = 8.56
  - Commit Handler:            Σ BPS = 4.96

System Aggregate BPS: 5.82 (HIGH - Requires active monitoring)
```

