# A-CFO-SolvencyAudit Technical Specification

## 1. Core Logic Definition

### 1.1 Solvency Audit Function

```
SolvencyScore(t) = Σ[w_i × R_i(t)] / Σ[w_i × L_i(t)] × AdjustmentFactor(t)

Where:
  R_i(t) = Realizable Asset Value at time t for asset class i
  L_i(t) = Liability Obligation at time t for liability class i
  w_i = Weight coefficient per asset/liability class
  AdjustmentFactor(t) = 1 - (VolatilityPenalty + LiquidityDiscount + ConcentrationRisk)
```

### 1.2 Primary Solvency Ratios

| Ratio | Formula | Critical Threshold |
|-------|---------|-------------------|
| Current Ratio | `CA / CL` | ≥ 1.5 |
| Quick Ratio | `(CA - Inventory) / CL` | ≥ 1.0 |
| Cash Ratio | `(Cash + MarketableSecurities) / CL` | ≥ 0.2 |
| Debt-to-Equity | `TotalDebt / ShareholderEquity` | ≤ 2.0 |
| Interest Coverage | `EBIT / InterestExpense` | ≥ 3.0 |
| Debt Service Coverage | `NOI / TotalDebtService` | ≥ 1.25 |

### 1.3 Composite Solvency Index (CSI)

```
CSI = (0.25 × NormalizedCurrentRatio) + 
      (0.20 × NormalizedQuickRatio) + 
      (0.15 × NormalizedCashRatio) + 
      (0.20 × InverseNormalizedDTE) + 
      (0.10 × NormalizedICR) + 
      (0.10 × NormalizedDSCR)

Normalization: N(x) = min(1, max(0, (x - x_min) / (x_max - x_min)))
```

---

## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Category Definitions

```
BPS = Σ(ImpactScore × ProbabilityScore × DetectionDifficulty) / MaxPossibleScore × 100
```

### 2.2 Operational Failure Risk Matrix

| Risk ID | Failure Mode | Impact (1-10) | Probability (1-10) | Detection (1-10) | BPS | Mitigation Priority |
|---------|--------------|---------------|-------------------|------------------|-----|---------------------|
| BPS-001 | Data Feed Latency > 5min | 8 | 6 | 3 | 14.4 | P1 |
| BPS-002 | Asset Valuation Stale > 24h | 9 | 4 | 4 | 14.4 | P1 |
| BPS-003 | Liability Sync Failure | 10 | 3 | 5 | 15.0 | P0 |
| BPS-004 | FX Rate Desync | 7 | 5 | 4 | 14.0 | P2 |
| BPS-005 | Calculation Engine Timeout | 8 | 4 | 2 | 6.4 | P2 |
| BPS-006 | Threshold Alert Suppression | 9 | 2 | 7 | 12.6 | P1 |
| BPS-007 | Audit Trail Corruption | 10 | 1 | 8 | 8.0 | P1 |
| BPS-008 | Regulatory Report Delay | 9 | 3 | 3 | 8.1 | P1 |
| BPS-009 | Multi-Entity Aggregation Error | 8 | 4 | 6 | 19.2 | P0 |
| BPS-010 | Historical Data Truncation | 7 | 2 | 5 | 7.0 | P3 |

### 2.3 BPS Threshold Classification

```
BPS Range    | Classification | Response SLA | Escalation Level
-------------|----------------|--------------|------------------
0.0 - 5.0    | LOW            | 72h          | L1 Operations
5.1 - 10.0   | MODERATE       | 24h          | L2 Engineering
10.1 - 15.0  | HIGH           | 4h           | L3 SRE + Finance
15.1 - 20.0  | CRITICAL       | 1h           | P0 Incident
> 20.0       | CATASTROPHIC   | 15min        | Executive + Regulatory
```

### 2.4 Cascade Failure Probability Model

```
P(CascadeFailure) = 1 - Π(1 - P_i × DependencyWeight_i)

DependencyGraph:
  DataIngestion → Valuation → Calculation → Reporting → Alerting

  Edge Weights:
    DataIngestion → Valuation: 0.95
    Valuation → Calculation: 0.90
    Calculation → Reporting: 0.85
    Reporting → Alerting: 0.80
```

